{\par \b Syntax:}\par limit(Expr,Var,Val)\par
{\par \b Description:}\par Limit of an expression as a variable approaches a value. Returns the limit (2 sided or 1-sided) of the given expression as the given variable approaches a value.\par
{\par \b Example:}\par limit((n*tan(x)-tan(n*x))/(sin(n*x)-n*sin(x)),x,0) returns 2\par }